# Docs sync

Docs ship in the **same** change as what they describe. See
`references/docs-sync-policy.md` for the per-change-type targets.

## The rule of thumb

If a change alters behavior, structure, or policy, update the relevant docs and
task records in the same PR. Keep docs factual (current state). Fix every link
when files move (prefer repo-root-relative `/path` links).

## Enforce

- Link integrity: `python3 {{CHECKS_DIR}}/check_doc_links.py --root . --strict`
- "Change X ⇒ update doc Y" rules live in `{{RULES_FILE}}`, checked by
  `python3 {{CHECKS_DIR}}/check_docs_sync.py --root .`

